[Site Skill: Google Maps]
SITE SKILL — Google Maps

## DOM
- Results live in article elements inside [role='feed']
- Name: a[href*='/place/'] · Rating/reviews: img[alt*='stars'] (alt = '4.5 stars 123 Reviews') · Category: button:nth-of-type(2)
- Scroll target is [role='feed'], NOT window — window scroll does nothing

## PROCESS
1. Confirm list view — if 0, you are in place-detail, go back:
   browser_evaluate { function: "document.querySelectorAll('article').length" }

2. Init buffer (once):
   browser_evaluate { function: "(function(){ localStorage.setItem('__orb__','[]'); return 'ok'; })()" }

3. Extract + append after every scroll — returns {total, added}:
   browser_evaluate { function: "(function(){ var d=JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('__orb__')||'[]'); var seen=new Set(d.map(function(x){return x.name;})); var added=0; Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('article')).forEach(function(el){ var name=(el.querySelector('a[href*=\"/place/\"]')||{}).textContent||''; if(!name.trim()||seen.has(name.trim()))return; seen.add(name.trim()); var alt=(el.querySelector('img[alt*=\"stars\"]')||{}).alt||''; d.push({name:name.trim(),rating:(alt.match(/([\d.]+)\s*stars/i)||[])[1]||'',reviews:(alt.match(/(\d+)\s*Reviews/i)||[])[1]||'',category:(el.querySelectorAll('button')[1]||{}).textContent||''}); added++; }); localStorage.setItem('__orb__',JSON.stringify(d)); return {total:d.length,added:added}; })()" }

4. Scroll the feed:
   browser_evaluate { function: "(function(){ var f=document.querySelector('[role=feed]'); f.scrollTop+=800; return f.scrollTop; })()" }

5. Repeat steps 3–4. Stop when added===0 twice in a row.

6. Save:
   save_csv { storageKey: "__orb__", filename: "maps-results" }
   save_json { storageKey: "__orb__", filename: "maps-results" }

## RULES
- browser_evaluate = single expression only. Multi-statement → wrap in (function(){...})()
- No arrow functions inside eval — use function(){}
- Adapt the fields in step 3 to match what the user asked for

